 clean and everything through the next step is exactly right — don't touch any of it. The closing is the one thing still not quite there. 'You'll know exactly where to pick up' is better than what we had, but it still feels like a promise of clarity rather than clarity itself. The reader finishes and thinks 'okay, I'll wait' — but what I want them to think is 'I already know what I'm doing the moment that plan hits.' Can you make that last line feel less like 'you'll be ready' and more like 'you're already in motion'? Think less reassurance, more ignition.

